			<div class='technique-name'>Trauma/PTSD Therapy</div><hr>
			<div class='technique-content'>
				<p>Learn to overcome psychological trauma. Trauma exists when a person perceives threat and his/her ability to handle the event has been impaired.</p>

				<p>Some common trauma and stressor-related disorders include:
					<ul>
						<li>Adjustment disorders Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD)</li>
						<li>Acute stress disorder (ASD)</li>
						<li>Reactive attachment disorder (RAD)</li>
						<li>Disinhibited social engagement disorder (DSED)</li>
					</ul>
				</p>

				<p>Treatment Goals:
					<ul>
						<li>To help you become aware of your feelings</li>
						<li>To help you face the reality of the traumatic event without getting stuck in it</li>
						<li>To decrease or eradicate trauma symptoms</li>
						<li>To work towards shifting focus from the past to the present</li>
						<li>To improve daily functioning</li>
						<li>To help you reclaim your personal power</li>
						<li>To help you overcome addictions associated with traumatic stress</li>
						<li>To help you gain skills that prevent relapse</li>
					</ul>
				</p>

				<p>Treatment Modalities:
					<ul>
						<li>Individual Psychotherapy</li>
						<li>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy</li>
						<li>Prolonged Exposure Therapy</li>
						<li>Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR)</li>
						<li>Hypnotherapy</li>
						<li>Psychodynamic Therapy</li>
						<li>Group Therapy</li>
					</ul>
				</p>

		</div>
	</div>


		<div class="tab-pane fade" id="depression">
			<div class='technique-name'>Depression Therapy</div><hr>
			<div class='technique-content'>
				<p>Learn to address the causes of persistent feeling of sadness and loss of interest.  Learning that depression is not a weakness and that stopping unpleasant or negative feelings may require long-term treatment is important.</p>

				<p>Common types of depressive disorders are:
					<li>Major Depressive Disorder (Clinical Depression)</li>
					<li>Persistent Depressive Disorder</li>
					<li>Bipolar Disorder</li>
					<li>Postpartum Depression</li>
					<li>Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder</li>
					<li>Seasonal Affective Disorder</li>
					<li>Atypical Depression</li>
				</p>

				<p>Treatment Goals:
					<li>Develop a safety plan</li>
					<li>Become involved pleasurable or enjoyable activities</li>
					<li>Decrease reports of suicidal ideation</li>
					<li>Learn coping skills, including problem solving and emotional regulation</li>
					<li>Identify maladaptive, negative thoughts and replace them with more positive, adaptive thoughts</li>
				</p>

				<p>Treatment Modalities
					<li>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy</li>
					<li>Interpersonal Therapy</li>
					<li>Psychodynamic Therapy</li>
					<li>Social Skills Therapy</li>
					<li>Supportive Counseling</li>
					<li>Behavioral Activation</li>
					<li>Problem-Solving Therapy</li>
				</p>
